      "bio": "Rav Rechumi III was an early Savora who edited and completed the Babylonian Talmud after the Amoraic period. According to Rav Sherira Gaon, he died in Nisan 506. He was a student of Rabbah Tosfa'ah and engaged in halakhic discourse with Rabbah Yosei, head of the Pumbedita yeshiva; one of their disputes concerning the meaning of \"petchei shima'i\" is cited twice in the Talmud, in Eruvin and Menachot. He is called \"the Third\" because two earlier Amoraim also bore the name Rav Rechumi. Some scholars identify him with the Talmudic figure Rav Nechumi (or Rav Nechumai), who argues with Rabbah about courtyard eruv, or with Rabbi Nechunya, who inquires about treifot in Eretz Yisrael.",
